{
  "stem": "26728.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I played in the regimental band with a bugle, and I got to be a bugler temporarily.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that-- another other guy who was better than me won out that job.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was a cushy job, to be the bugler.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was temporarily assigned to a machine gun squad, and I was a, a gunner and a-- and a driver of a 3/4 ton truck.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "These were when they were getting to be mobile as opposed to walking.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That didn't last very long.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Most people have never heard of the big maneuvers of 1941 in Louisiana.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We-- this was the biggest, up to that point in time, military maneuvers ever held in this country by the United States Army.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were literally, by then, millions of soldiers, aviators involved in the maneuvers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that was really a test.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If you could handle that in the summertime, in the jungles, it-- which is where-- we thought, you know, we were going to end up in the South Pacific.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this is still 1941.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The maneuvers were still going on in September.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I-- my year-- I had a one-year contract with the Army of United States, and they had to let me out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Had I been drafted, it was for the duration.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So, in the-- I was kind of like the cadre, which I mentioned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "A cadre is-- is-- is-- is kind of like the skeleton of a-- of an organization, and the bo-- the meat is the draftees.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So the cadre comes in, the cadre forms the foundation of the organization, and the draftees come in and flesh it out under the training of the cadre men.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I was a cadre person.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
